b"This Transgender Awareness Week we are calling attention to our fierce, fabulous trans talent by putting them front and center with these gorgeous portraits by artist @katemoross. 

We live in a world that simultaneously erases trans excellence while benefitting from trans art, culture, and contributions, especially when it comes to trans people of color. It's especially important for cis queer people to celebrate the trans folks living and creating in our community, to uplift them and pass the mic when needed. 

Media can help raise awareness, and we as a community have a responsibility to look out for each other and provide resources to the most vulnerable among us. Let's also remember to celebrate trans folks every month, every week, and every day."

b"how is it that questions like, \xe2\x80\x9cHow are you?\xe2\x80\x9d and \xe2\x80\x9cAre you okay?\xe2\x80\x9d are sometimes such hard questions to answer. If you\xe2\x80\x99ve really gone through it, how can you sum up your problems to someone casually checking in? There\xe2\x80\x99s something so relatable and calming about Dom + Joey\xe2\x80\x99s reunion in Grand Army. Both characters have been through such life changing events since they last saw each other, yet all they can bring to the table is, \xe2\x80\x9cI\xe2\x80\x99m fine.\xe2\x80\x9d I'm sure you've been at the point where all you can offer is, \xe2\x80\x9cI\xe2\x80\x99m fine.\xe2\x80\x9d It\xe2\x80\x99s that point of exhaustion, where all the tears have been cried and all the yells have been shouted and even though the world has been cruel to you, you don\xe2\x80\x99t have the energy to be angry at it anymore. b'\xe2\x80\x9cD\xc3\xada de Muertos is a tradition I would like to keep alive,\xe2\x80\x9d says @ajuliomacias to @contodonetflix about the culture he plans to pass down to his family. \xe2\x80\x9cIt full-heartedly celebrates death as just another chapter in the ever-flowing experience that is the human soul. It teaches you from an early age to accept it without fear, and understand it with love. You celebrate those who have passed by communing with them once a year, sharing their favorite foods and music, telling their stories, turning something most people see as mournful into something magical.\xe2\x80\x9d\n\nart by @marianopeccinetti'
